==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zoanthus
<hw>Zo*an"thus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Zoantharia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
Actinaria, including numerous species, found mostly in tropical seas.
The zooids or polyps resemble small, elongated actinias united together
at their bases by fleshy stolons, and thus forming extensive groups. The
tentacles are small and bright colored.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

